<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Amrel yr shr falls, div steady.</title>
<headline>Amrel yr shr falls, div steady.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)	   121	vs     136</p>
<p>    - adjusted shr (cts)	121	vs     107</p>
<p>    Div (cts)			34	vs     34</p>
<p>    Attrib income	     38.44	vs     41.63</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		     60.42	vs     52.00</p>
<p>    Tax			   21.78	vs     18.63</p>
<p>    Finance costs	     52.81	vs     53.03</p>
<p>    Turnover		 1,024.79	vs  1,245.78</p>
<p>    Share of associates'     0.20	vs     0.36</p>
<p>Div payable July 2</p>
<p>on register May 30</p>
<p>Full name: Amalgamated Retail Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said attributable earnings of 38.4 million rand represented earnings per share of 121 cents, an increase of 13 percent, excluding the rate adjustment on the deferred tax liability in the prior year.</p>
<p>It said unless consumption for durables increased over the second half of the financial year, it would be difficult to improve much on the current level of earnings.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
</text>
